level’ saying, ‘It’s favorable! Krishna

218
00:28:11,789 --> 00:28:19,130
is not trying to take you down but rather
to promote you.’” So therefore, in that

219
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:24,350
sense — friendly. “That’s when,” he’s
saying, “the environment is friendly.”

220
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:29,929
But it’s a way of seeing.
What is the first mantra, the primal guru-mantra?

221
00:28:29,929 --> 00:28:35,710
Oṁ ajñāna-timirāndhasya jñānāñjana-śalākayā
chakṣur unmilitaṁ yena. It’s saying,

222
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:44,731
“My eyes were cataracted with ignorance,
acquired prejudice, acquired tendency so I’m

223
00:28:44,731 --> 00:29:03,529
not seeing clearly.” Like surgical removal.
Lasers now, they remove cataracts. So, I like

224
00:29:03,529 --> 00:29:16,029
that because it’s light. “By light, enlightened,
I’m expressing my gratitude to Śrī Guru

225
00:29:16,029 --> 00:29:20,999
who opened my eyes that were cataracted with
ignorance. I wasn’t seeing myself and my

226
00:29:20,999 --> 00:29:25,210
life circumstances properly.”

227
00:29:25,210 --> 00:29:35,200
Guru Mahārāja also gave an example unlike
a very high level. Not that we should imitate

228
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:42,259
but we should be aware. And it’s whole in
the life of Śrīla Gaura-Kiśora Dās Bābājī

229
00:29:42,259 --> 00:29:50,659
Mahārāja. Like we heard about Śukadeva
Goswāmī. We think he’s so beautiful and

230
00:29:50,659 --> 00:29:57,100
such a charming figure but on his way to the
assembly of Parikṣit Mahārāja, on the

231
00:29:57,100 --> 00:30:08,669
banks of Jamunā where the Bhāgavatam was
spoken, on his way there, children were throwing

232
00:30:08,669 --> 00:30:14,840
